y, Sampford Peverell, and Sampford Spiney (all Devon), Sampford Arundel and Sampford Brett (both Somerset), and Sandford (Shropshire). See also   Sandiford  ."]}]},{"name":"Hugh","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French name, <i>Hugues</i>, <i>Hugo</i>, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>hug</i> ‘heart, mind, spirit’. It was originally a short form of various compound names containing this element. This was borne by the aristocracy of medieval France, adopted by the Normans, and introduced by them to Britain. It was consistently one of the most popular boys' names in the Middle Ages in England, but fell out of favour in the 16th century until it was revived in the 20th century. Little Hugh of Lincoln was a child supposed in the Middle Ages to have been murdered by Jews in about  1255 , a legend responsible for several outbursts of anti-Semitism at various times. The story is referred to by  Chaucer  in The Prioress's Tale. He is not to be confused with  St Hugh of Lincoln  (  1140–1200 ), bishop of Lincoln (  1186–1200 ), who was noted for his charity and good works, his piety, and his defence of the Church against the State. Since the later Middle Ages <i>Hugh</i> has also been used as an Anglicized form of the Gaelic name Aodh ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705188,"age":3,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":38,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705190,"age":69,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Hugh Sanford was born about 1221, in Leighton, Shropshire, England. He had at least 1 daughter with Mrs. Hugh Sanford."},"et":{"Abt 1221–":"umbes 1221–Surnud","1225–Female":"1225–Surnud","1247–Female":"1247–Surnud","1221–Male":"1221–Surnud","1259":"1259","1247":"1247","1225":"1225","1224":"1224","Abt 1221":"umbes 1221","1221":"1221","1290":"1290","Leighton, Shropshire, England":"Leighton, Shropshire, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1221–":"noin 1221–Kuollut","1225–Female":"1225–Kuollut","1247–Female":"1247–Kuollut","1221–Male":"1221–Kuollut","1259":"1259","1247":"1247","1225":"1225","1224":"1224","Abt 1221":"noin 1221","1221":"1221","1290":"1290","Leighton, Shropshire, England":"Leighton, Shropshire, England"},"fr":{"Abt 1221–":"environ 1221–Décédé","1225–Female":"1225–Décédée","1247–Female":"1247–Décédée","1221–Male":"1221–Décédé","1259":"1259","1247":"1247","1225":"1225","1224":"1224","Abt 1221":"environ 1221","1221":"1221","1290":"1290","Leighton, Shropshire, England":"Leighton, Shropshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Hugh Sanford est né environ 1221, à Leighton, Shropshire, Angleterre. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Mrs. Hugh Sanford."},"de":{"Abt 1221–":"um 1221–Verstorben","1225–Female":"1225–Verstorben","1247–Female":"1247–Verstorben","1221–Male":"1221–Verstorben","1259":"1259","1247":"1247","1225":"1225","1224":"1224","Abt 1221":"um 1221","1221":"1221","1290":"1290","Leighton, Shropshire, England":"Leighton, Shropshire, England","lifeSummary":"Hugh Sanford wurde um 1221 in Leighton, Shropshire, England geboren. Er hatte mit Mrs. Hugh Sanford mindestens 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"Abt 1221–":"about 1221–Desede","1225–Female":"1225–Desede","1247–Female":"1247–Desede","1221–Male":"1221–Desede","1259":"1259","1247":"1247","1225":"1225","1224":"1